# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionKingdom12CouncilRule
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "When they finally reconvened, a heavy atmosphere seemed to hang over the room."
    new "When they finally reconvened, a heavy atmosphere seemed to hang over the room."

    old "Maeiv was the first to assert herself."
    new "Maeiv was the first to assert herself."

    old "We are gathered here again to settle this final matter. The most important matter of all."
    new "We are gathered here again to settle this final matter. The most important matter of all."

    old "She paused as she looked about the room."
    new "She paused as she looked about the room."

    old "Who will rule over our Union."
    new "Who will rule over our Union."

    old "She tapped the table."
    new "She tapped the table."

    old "I do not doubt that each of you has considered themselves for the role, but I would like us all to put aside our personal interests."
    new "I do not doubt that each of you has considered themselves for the role, but I would like us all to put aside our personal interests."

    old "Instead, I would ask you all to support myself for the role."
    new "Instead, I would ask you all to support myself for the role."

    old "Sarah could see the others shake their head in disbelief."
    new "Sarah could see the others shake their head in disbelief."

    old "No surprise there!"
    new "No surprise there!"

    old "For once I agree with Antonio, of course you want the position for yourself."
    new "For once I agree with Antonio, of course you want the position for yourself."

    old "You are ambitious to a fault."
    new "You are ambitious to a fault."

    old "Maeiv only smiled at their comments."
    new "Maeiv only smiled at their comments."

    old "I understand you reactions, but let us be fair."
    new "I understand you reactions, but let us be fair."

    old "It was I who detected the Mythran invasion. I was the one who set out to put together this Union Council."
    new "It was I who detected the Mythran invasion. I was the one who set out to put together this Union Council."

    old "Out of all of us, I am most prepared to face this attack."
    new "Out of all of us, I am most prepared to face this attack."

    old "She was quick to add a last comment."
    new "She was quick to add a last comment."

    old "And of course, I will take on the mantle for only a brief moment. Until our Union is safe. Then I will relinquish all this power again."
    new "And of course, I will take on the mantle for only a brief moment. Until our Union is safe. Then I will relinquish all this power again."

    old "Sarah could hear the others scoff. Few believed her."
    new "Sarah could hear the others scoff. Few believed her."

    old "The others all looked at her, surprised by her sudden motion."
    new "The others all looked at her, surprised by her sudden motion."

    old "Queen Maeiv...you speak the truth. You detected this threat."
    new "Queen Maeiv...you speak the truth. You detected this threat."

    old "But, you say that we must be frank, and so I will be just that."
    new "But, you say that we must be frank, and so I will be just that."

    old "The truth is that our differences, as much as we have discussed and debated, still remain."
    new "The truth is that our differences, as much as we have discussed and debated, still remain."

    old "Most of us here, even now, do not trust each other."
    new "Most of us here, even now, do not trust each other."

    old "Sarah paused as she looked about the room and saw that each of them agreed."
    new "Sarah paused as she looked about the room and saw that each of them agreed."

    old "We are all fools if we imagine that the four of us would undo centuries of distrust between our nations. Our peoples."
    new "We are all fools if we imagine that the four of us would undo centuries of distrust between our nations. Our peoples."

    old "Only now, with the threat of invasion, are we even somewhat unified."
    new "Only now, with the threat of invasion, are we even somewhat unified."

    old "Sarah placed the palms of her hands on the table."
    new "Sarah placed the palms of her hands on the table."

    old "Instead, I propose that our government structure reflects the truth of our Union."
    new "Instead, I propose that our government structure reflects the truth of our Union."

    old "We are divided. So let us rule. Not as one, but as many different parts of a whole."
    new "We are divided. So let us rule. Not as one, but as many different parts of a whole."

    old "I propose that our Union shall be governed by a Council, much like this one."
    new "I propose that our Union shall be governed by a Council, much like this one."

    old "Sarah saw Maeiv's face drop."
    new "Sarah saw Maeiv's face drop."

    old "No, I don't think that's an option. We must decide on a single ruler."
    new "No, I don't think that's an option. We must decide on a single ruler."

    old "By whose word?"
    new "By whose word?"

    old "Her question was answered only with silence."
    new "Her question was answered only with silence."

    old "We are each the rulers of our nations. We set the rules for this new Union that we are creating. It is whatever we say it to be."
    new "We are each the rulers of our nations. We set the rules for this new Union that we are creating. It is whatever we say it to be."

    old "Sarah could see the others nod."
    new "Sarah could see the others nod."

    old "Each understood that perhaps they would have liked to be in charge, but each also understood they would never gain enough support."
    new "Each understood that perhaps they would have liked to be in charge, but each also understood they would never gain enough support."

    old "At least now, they would all have a share of the power."
    new "At least now, they would all have a share of the power."

    old "Antonio was the first to speak up."
    new "Antonio was the first to speak up."

    old "An excellent proposal, Sarah. I will support it."
    new "An excellent proposal, Sarah. I will support it."

    old "My preference would have been for a single ruler, but if the choice is between power-hungry politicians or a Council, I will support the latter."
    new "My preference would have been for a single ruler, but if the choice is between power-hungry politicians or a Council, I will support the latter."

    old "You have my support as well, Sarah."
    new "You have my support as well, Sarah."

    old "Sarah looked at Queen Maeiv. She could see that she had lost."
    new "Sarah looked at Queen Maeiv. She could see that she had lost."

    old "Think that is a wonderful idea, Sarah."
    new "Think that is a wonderful idea, Sarah."

    old "Now that the room had shifted in favor of Sarah's position, Maeiv was quick to turn with the shifting winds."
    new "Now that the room had shifted in favor of Sarah's position, Maeiv was quick to turn with the shifting winds."

    old "Excellent, then it is decided by unanimous consent."
    new "Excellent, then it is decided by unanimous consent."

    old "The others banged the table to voice their support."
    new "The others banged the table to voice their support."

    old "Even Maeiv, reluctantly, joined in."
    new "Even Maeiv, reluctantly, joined in."

